At the press of a button
any civil servant

21
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:44,518
can inspect just about
every detail of your life

22
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:48,070
yourtax, yourmedical record,
periods of unemployment,

23
00:01:48,240 --> 00:01:51,277
children's school records,
and that civil servant

24
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:53,396
may happen to be
yourneighbour.

25
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:56,593
There's been mounting concern
overthis powerful,

26
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:59,513
even totalitarian weapon
that the computerrevolution

27
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:01,557
has put into
the Government's hand.

28
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:04,632
And the man who wields
the weapon is the Minister

29
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:08,588
forAdministrative Affairs,
the Right Honourable James Hacker.

30
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:12,437
Now, Minister, are we laying
the foundations of a police state?

31
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:16,475
You know, I'm glad
you asked me that question.

32
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:20,310
Well, Minister,
could we have the answer?

33
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:24,719
Well, yes of course, I'm about
to give it to you, if I may.

34
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:27,709
As I said, I'm glad
you asked me that question.

35
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:28,880
Because...

36
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:31,394
it's a question

37
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,951
a lot of people are asking.

38
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,120
And why?

39
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:38,996
Because a lot of people
want to know the answerto it.

40
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:43,154
And let's be quite clearabout this
without beating about the bush,

41
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:46,034
the plain fact of the matter is

42
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:49,796
that it's a very important
question indeed

43
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:52,316
and people have
a right to know.

44
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:58,192
But Minister, we haven't
yet had the answer.

45
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:01,351
I'm sorry,
whatwas the question?

46
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:05,277
Now look, supposing
I annoy you in this interview,

47
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:07,829
how do I know
you won't go back to youroffice,

48
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,514
press a button
and call up my tax records,

49
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:13,353
my hospital records,
my police record...

50
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,635
Oh no. No. No.

51
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:17,473
Bob, that's not the way
we do things in this country.

52
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:21,269
What's the Data Base for
if it's not to check up on people?

53
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,837
You know, that's
a very interesting question.

54
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:29,315
It's forstoring information

55
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:32,677
so as to speed up
government business

56
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:37,078
so thatwe need not take on
an enormous influx of clerical staff.

57
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:40,755
Computers are big business
and are good news.

58
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:44,072
But, Minister, if you put
information into the machine,

59
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:46,993
you'll eventually take information
out of the machine.

60
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,958
Not necessarily.

61
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:53,718
So, you're going to spend
25 million pounds

62
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:55,871
accumulating information
and neveruse it?

63
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:58,597
No. Yes. No.

64
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:02,040
Well, there will be safeguards.

65
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,269
Such as?

66
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:06,595
Close in on him, Two.
Bob's got him on the run.

67
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,153
One minute 45, studio.

68
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:11,357
We'll be looking
at a whole range of possibilities.

69
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:15,230
And of course, it's a complex
and highly technical matter.

70
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,277
Rome wasn't built in a day.

71
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,794
It's underreview.

72
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:22,269
And of course,
these things take time.

73
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:25,876
Minister, am I talking
to the formereditorof Reform

74
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,792
orto a Civil Service spokesman?

75
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:30,713
We haven't talked about
the safeguards I've introduced.

76
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:34,077
And there's my newbureaucratic
watchdog office, for instance.

77
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,158
It does look as if we'll need

78
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:38,595
